source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/lobster-ravioli-in-a-lemony-cream-sauce-62bb148ab6a0f47c72077162
servings: 2
---

Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil.

Heat a large, dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer bacon to a #paper-towel lined plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop. Wipe out pan.

While bacon cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve and peel @shallot{1}; finely chop half the shallot. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in pan used for bacon over medium-high heat. Add @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until lightly charred and beginning to burst, ~{2-3%minutes}. (If tomatoes haven't burst yet, gently press them with a #spatula.) Turn off heat; transfer to plate.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} and a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add shallot and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, a pinch of salt, and pepper.

Once water is boiling, add @lobster ravioli{9%ounce} to #pot and reduce heat to low. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then gently drain.

Meanwhile, heat @butter{1%tablespoon} in a small, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} and cook, stirring, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper. Set aside.

Return pan with sauce to low heat. Stir in blistered tomatoes, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, lemon zest, 1/3 cup reserved pasta cooking water (1/2 cup for 4 servings), and juice from half the lemon. Cook, stirring occasionally and gently crushing some of the tomatoes, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in half the @spinach{5%ounce}; cook until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add drained ravioli and @butter{1%tablespoon}; gently stir until butter has melted and ravioli is coated in a creamy sauce. (If necessary, stir in more pasta cooking water a splash at a time.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

In a large #bowl, toss bacon, half the @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, remaining spinach, juice from remaining lemon, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}. Top with half the panko. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide ravioli between bowls. Sprinkle with remaining panko and remaining Parmesan. Serve with spinach salad on the side.